blurb: F# is a strongly-typed, functional language that is part of Microsoft's .NET language stack. Although F# is great for data science problems, it can elegantly handle almost every problem you throw at it.

key_features.title: Expressive
key_features.content: F# code is very expressive, requiring little code for great results

key_features.title: Fun
key_features.content: F#'s powerful type system is a joy to work with

key_features.title: Safe
key_features.content: F#'s type system helps catch errors at compile-time. No more null-reference exceptions!

key_features.title: Functional first
key_features.content: F# is primarily a functional language, but also has great object-oriented support

key_features.title: Interop
key_features.content: As a member of the .NET ecosystem, F# enjoys full, two-way compatibility with C# code/libraries

key_features.title: Tooling
key_features.content: F# has excellent tooling, with linting and refactoring options built-in
